I, for one, appreciate your standing up for many of us who have simply tired of fighting the same battles with the same people for the same old reasons.<br>
<br>
The thing that truly saddens me about all the misguided loathing that spews forth on this board directed at this or that guild or individual for some perceived misdeed, is so often the result of conflict between people of similar interests and desires who would, in other circumstances, be the closest friends and allies.<br>
<br>
I am so tired of the constant pointless bashing of guilds (and individuals) that have passed into memory. (RoS, CIW, KEG, and any number of others) Perhaps someone could post a legitimate reason why doing so is necessary, other than to feed the low self-esteem of some individuals by denegrating others.<br>
<br>
Finally, to the point at hand, it is an unfortunate occurrence, and I am terribly sorry for Calh.<br>
<br>
I'm sure, however, that SoF did not zone into Skyfire with the intent to deprive Calh of the fruits of his long camp.<br>
<br>
Clearly, a bad situation that was engineered by the designers at Verant was made worse by a series of miscommunications between guilds and individuals.<br>
<br>
SoF, it appears, made a mistake. And I hope people can see fit to forgive them. Conversely, I would expect the leaders and members of SoF to have the grace to admit their mistake and attempt to make amends in some way.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion...I'm sure everyone will disagree.   <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69312"><b>Kolwyn Calacolindor</b></a>,<br>
